<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6119&amp;p=57591#p57591</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6119&amp;p=57591#p57591"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Doing a custom mapper - feasibility?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6119&amp;p=57591#p57591"><![CDATA[
The consensus at the bottom of the previous topic appears to suggest the following: <ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Get a PowerPak and a sufficiently recent Windows PC. </li><li>Download and install Visual Studio Express and the FPGA devkit. </li><li>Start from the CNROM demo source and write your own mapper for PowerPak. </li><li>Once it's working on a PowerPak, write patches for FCEUX, Nestopia, and Nintendulator. </li><li>Post all this on nesdev BBS, and people on this board <em>might</em> help you reduce it to a CPLD-based design that you can replicate. </li></ol><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Mar 05, 2010 5:41 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
