<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6119&amp;p=57585#p57585"><![CDATA[
We have talked many times about a new mapper for the homebrew community, but there seems to be a chicken vs egg kinda thing going on: nobody wants to program a game for a mapper that doesn't exist and nobody wants to make a mapper for which no games exist.<br /><br />A while ago there was an interesting <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=51785#51785" class="postlink">idea proposed by tepples</a>, which was a very versatile mapper, but that seems to have gone nowhere.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Fri Mar 05, 2010 4:20 pm</p><hr />
