<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6119&amp;p=57580#p57580</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6119&amp;p=57580#p57580"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Doing a custom mapper - feasibility?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6119&amp;p=57580#p57580"><![CDATA[
One thing you could try: Start with MMC1, such as the MMC1 clone from retrousb.com, and swap the CHR A12 and A11 lines going into the CHR ROM chip. Then register $A000 controls 2 KB banks in $0000 and $1000, and register $C000 controls 2 KB banks in $0800 and $1800.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Mar 05, 2010 2:27 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
